                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 181.9202/222: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to General <persName type="to">Bandholtz</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-20T21:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 20, 1919—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>110. Your 189, November 6, 1919.<note n="74" xml:id="d353fn74">Not
                        printed.</note> The Department advises that Ulysses Grant-Smith has been
                    selected as Commissioner to Hungary and instructed to proceed immediately.
                    Grant-Smith is at present a Counselor of Embassy in the Diplomatic Service in
                    which he has served for 16 years. He has served in the former Embassy at Vienna
                    for about 4 years in the capacity of Secretary and also as Counselor. He
                    recently served as Chargé d’Affaires of the Legation at Copenhagen. He is now in
                    the United States. This is for your confidential information and is not to be
                    given out until made public by the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
